					<div class="grid_1"><img src="{{ asset('bundles/fibehomepage/img/picto/like.png') }}" /></div>
					<div class="grid_3"><p>Let people find what they liked using the app.</p></div>
					</div>
				</div>
				</a>
			</div>
		</div>

		<div id="before">
			<div class="container_12">
				<h1>Before Conference</h1>
				<div class="illustration"></div>
				<div id="overview01" class="clearfix">
					<div class="grid_1"><img src="{{ asset('bundles/fibehomepage/img/picto/import.png') }}" /></div>
					<div class="number grid_1">1.</div>
					<div class="grid_3"><h3>Start from scratch or import your OCS data.</h3></div>
				</div>
				<div class="explain grid_4 clearfix">
					<p><span class="logoname"><b>Live</b>con</span>  provide  you an import fonctionnality, which let you start from your OCS data or from scratch. Your live conference is a set of sub event following a web standard hierarchy that can managed thanks to a visual calendar by specifying :<br/>
					<b>Who :</b> The actors involved in each of your event and their roles (chair, speaker…).<br/>
					<b>What :</b> The papers presented associated with their authors, a main theme and a format (talk, panel, session, workshop, tutorial, break….).<br/>
					<b>Where :</b>  The room where the events take place.<br/>
					<b>When :</b> The date when the events take place.<br/><br/>
					Your mobile application is already available, customize it as you wish!</p>
				</div>
				<div id="overview02" class="clearfix">
					<div class="grid_1"><img src="{{ asset('bundles/fibehomepage/img/picto/custom.png') }}" /></div>
					<div class="number grid_1">2.</div>
					<div class="grid_3"><h3>Customize your mobile application as you wish.</h3></div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>

		<div id="during">
			<div class="container_12">
				<h1>During Conference</h1>
				<div class="grid_5 alpha omega">
					<div id="overview03" class="clearfix">
						<div class="clearfix">
						<div class="grid_1"><img src="{{ asset('bundles/fibehomepage/img/picto/schedule.png') }}" /></div>
						<div class="number grid_1">3.</div>
						<div class="grid_3"><h3>Keep your schedule up to date.</h3></div>
						</div>
						<div class="grid_3 push_2"><p>Planning changes? Speaker late?<br/>
							Change your schedule easily with a user friendly  interface.<br/>
							Plan speaker to a different event, move an event to an another room…</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div id="overview04" class="clearfix">
						<div class="clearfix">
						<div class="grid_1"><img src="{{ asset('bundles/fibehomepage/img/picto/reloaded.png') }}" /></div>
						<div class="number grid_1">4.</div>
						<div class="grid_3"><h3>Let the application broadcast the changes<br/>for you.</h3></div>
						</div>
						<div class="grid_3 push_2"><p>Thanks to your web application, all your changes will be broadcasted to your attendees that can consult the planning, the authors list, and everything that compose your conference directly from their smartphones.</p></div>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="grid_7"><img src="{{ asset('bundles/fibehomepage/img/illustration/during.png') }}" /></div>
			</div>
		</div>

		<div id="after">
			<div class="container_12">
				<h1>After Conference</h1>
				<div class="grid_6"><img src="{{ asset('bundles/fibehomepage/img/illustration/after.png') }}" /></div>
				<div class="grid_6">
					<div id="overview05" class="clearfix">
						<div class="clearfix">
						<div class="grid_1"><img src="{{ asset('bundles/fibehomepage/img/picto/publish.png') }}" /></div>
						<div class="number grid_1">5.</div>
						<div class="grid_4 omega"><h3>Open your data to the Web 3.0 and increase your conference visibility thanks to a SPARQL endpoint.</h3></div>
						</div>
						<div class="grid_4 push_2 omega"><p>By allowing people to have a Sparql access to your data, you can spread your conference name and expect even more attendees for your next event!</p></div>
					</div>
					<div id="overview06" class="clearfix">
						<div class="clearfix">
						<div class="grid_1"><img src="{{ asset('bundles/fibehomepage/img/picto/like.png') }}" /></div>
						<div class="number grid_1">6.</div>
						<div class="grid_4 omega"><h3>Let people find what they liked using the app.</h3></div>
						</div>
						<div class="grid_4 push_2 omega"><p>The application will remain available as long as you wish representing an amasing overview of what makes your conference a major actor of the domains it deals with.</p></div>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div></div>
			</div>
		</div>

		<div id="app">
			<div class="container_12">
				<h1>The <span class="logoname"><b>Live</b>con</span> App</h1>
				<div id="app01" class="grid_5">
					<iframe src="http://dataconf.liris.cnrs.fr/eswc2013/"></iframe>
